config.text: Number of Through Lanes

Summary:

Number of through lanes is to be derived by the striping, if present, on multilane facilities for each roadbed

Detailed Guidance:

Exclude all ramps and sections defined as auxiliary lanes, such as:

• Parking and dedicated turning lanes

• Toll collection lanes

• Truck climbing lanes

• Shoulders

• Continuous Center Turn Lanes

• Acceleration/Deceleration Lanes


A lane that exists as a weaving lane/auxiliary lane that exists for both entering and exiting a highway, and the distance from painted gore to painted gore is 0.3 miles or greater in length, is to be considered a through lane. See image below for clarification
Outside Shoulder Width

Summary:

Outside shoulder is considered the shoulder on the driver’s right when moving in the direction of travel.

Detailed Guidance:

  • For undivided roadways, which are only represented by a Single Roadbed, the Outside Shoulder is on the driver’s right and the direction of travel is determined by the ascending direction of M-values embedded in the linework of the provided feature class
  • Outside shoulder width should be measured to the nearest foot starting from the outer edge of the right-most through lane to the outer edge of the shoulder
  • Do not include parking or bicycle lanes in the shoulder width measurement
Inside Shoulder Width

Summary:

Inside shoulder is considered the shoulder on the driver’s left when moving in the direction of travel

Detailed Guidance:

For undivided roadways, which are only represented by a Single Roadbed, the Inside Shoulder is on the driver’s left and the direction of travel is determined by the ascending direction of M-values embedded in the linework of the provided feature class.


  • Inside shoulder width should be measured to the nearest foot starting from the outer edge of the left-most lane to the left-most edge of the shoulder
  • Do not include parking or bicycle lanes in the shoulder width measurement
Maximum Speed Limit

Summary:

Maximum Speed Limit is based on the posted speed limit along the roadway

Detailed Guidance:

• The Maximum Speed Limit will be recorded from the posted speed limit sign and continue until the next posted speed limit sign of a different speed limit along the same roadbed.


• For undivided roadways, which are only represented by a Single Roadbed, that have different posted speed limits for each side of the roadway, the posted speed limit for the route’s direction of travel is to be used


• Direction of travel is determined by the ascending direction of M-values embedded in the linework of the provided feature class

config.text:
Welcome to the RIVaL Data Collection Hub!

Check out the content and links below for a detailed explanation of this project, the current status and more information about how you can access the data and imagery.
﻿Project Status﻿
Our Collection Status Dashboard provides a dynamic view of your state's imagery and LiDAR collection﻿.
"Phase 0" Data Review

We want to ensure that we are providing your state with the highest quality extraction possible. DOT staff are encouraged to review and provide feedback on these extracted assets using our Data Review App.
Data Dictionary
The Data Dictionary provides a complete breakdown of the schema for our extracted assets. Both attributes and their corresponding values are defined for every extracted dataset.
Extraction Details

When extracting assets along your state's roadways, we do our utmost to adhere to the agreed upon data dictionary. However, there are always unexpected circumstances along the way which may fall outside of the norm. The Extraction Details log documents as many scenarios as we could find and provides our reasoning.
Project at-a-glance
Driving the Collection Area
For the RIVaL proof-of-concept (POC) demonstration, we drove along several roadways in Central Austin﻿
All Routes
100%
Completed
﻿Capture Imagery & LiDAR
A major part of the RIVaL project involves capturing high-resolution imagery and LIDaR at an interval of approximately every 5 meters for the entire collection area.
﻿A Total of
15,624
Images Captured
Asset Extraction

Using the 100 megapixel, 360 degree imagery, paired with our HD LIDaR, we extracted the 4 assets required by the RIVaL POC: Inside Shoulders, Outside Shoulders, Maximum Speed Limit and Number of Lanes
﻿A Total of
1,114
Assets Extracted
